summary: Prototype pollution vulnerability (CVE-2023-36665) in protobufjs transitive dependency with CVSS 5.5 score. The issue was automatically closed as the vulnerable library was no longer part of the inventory.
userImpact: Applications using client-1.8.0 may be vulnerable to prototype pollution attacks through protobufjs, potentially affecting availability.
rootCause: protobufjs versions 6.10.0 through 7.2.3 allow prototype pollution via untrusted protobuf messages or .proto files, enabling attackers to modify Object.prototype.
proposedFix: Upgrade protobufjs to version 7.2.4 or later
resolutionDetails: Automatically closed by Mend because the vulnerable library was no longer part of the inventory or was marked as ignored
keyQuote: protobufjs 6.10.0 through 7.x before 7.2.4 allows Prototype Pollution via user-controlled protobuf messages
